  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Older People to Improve Lives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishing 25 new OPAs in two districts | Organising management training and training in monitoring local government for all OPAs  | OPAs collect data on socioeconomic conditions of all older people in their villages, to compile at district level | OPAs, SRSO and HelpAge share data with social protection institutions to demonstrate need to make their services more accessible to vulnerable OP | Sensitisation workshops on ageing and rights of OP for private sector instits. running microcredit programmes and government officials | Microcredit grants given to 500 OPs - 80% do agricultural work to earn a living | 1500 OPs given training and toolkits to diversify livelihood to be less vulnerable to floods (kitchen garden/poultry/mushroom farming; livestock production; community based savings).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Older People</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve the mid-term food and livelihood security of 2000 disadvantaged older people and their families and to set in place structures and standards that improve older people&#x2019;s access to livelihoods support and social protection in the long term at provincial and national level.</narrative>
  </description>
